1
00:01:58,860 --> 00:02:00,120
<i>He's fast!</i>

2
00:02:03,910 --> 00:02:06,500
<i>Faster than anyone</i>
<i>I've ever fought before.</i>

3
00:02:20,050 --> 00:02:22,300
<i>And that sword…</i>

4
00:02:23,180 --> 00:02:25,600
<i>He uses the curve on the blade</i>

5
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:28,100
<i>to make up for the difference in reach.</i>

6
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:33,690
<i>You've got to be kidding me. He's unarmed!</i>

7
00:02:34,650 --> 00:02:37,570
<i>I'm a warrior from Miklagard,</i>
<i>for crying out loud.</i>

8
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:45,200
<i>"I have never once been glad," was it?</i>

9
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,250
<i>Jeez…</i>

10
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:53,000
<i>What kind of monsters</i>
<i>was he surrounded by?</i>

11
00:03:08,270 --> 00:03:09,560
<i>I'll keep hammering him.</i>

12
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,730
<i>You can't hit me!</i>

13
00:03:31,290 --> 00:03:32,580
<i>-He's strong.</i>
<i>-He's strong.</i>

14
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:38,090
<i>Why is such a skilled fighter</i>
<i>working as a bodyguard on a farm?</i>

15
00:03:38,670 --> 00:03:42,380
<i>How did a man like him become a slave?</i>

16
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:48,720
<i>No, I need to calm down.</i>
<i>I can't let him set the pace.</i>

17
00:03:50,060 --> 00:03:51,640
<i>All I need to do…</i>

18
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:05,530
<i>He can move even faster?</i>

19
00:04:09,910 --> 00:04:10,950
<i>I can see it.</i>

20
00:04:26,510 --> 00:04:27,760
<i>He got me.</i>

21
00:04:29,260 --> 00:04:30,890
<i>Gardar is…</i>

22
00:04:53,410 --> 00:04:54,960
-Snake!
-Don't do it, Snake!

23
00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:00,590
Don't kill…

24
00:05:02,090 --> 00:05:03,510
Gardar.

25
00:05:05,470 --> 00:05:06,630
Please…

26
00:05:07,470 --> 00:05:09,470
let him go.

27
00:05:16,940 --> 00:05:20,480
Get your head out of the clouds, Arnheid.

28
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:24,780
He killed five of my subordinates.

29
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:26,650
There's no way I can forgive him.

30
00:05:27,450 --> 00:05:34,040
Snake! I will do everything that I can
to honor the deaths of your subordinates.

31
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:37,460
-Even if that means selling my fields--
-Shut up, Gramps!

32
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:39,460
It's not about the money.

33
00:05:43,130 --> 00:05:46,590
It's true that
my subordinates and I are all

34
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:49,390
stupid, good-for-nothing,
small-time crooks.

35
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:55,390
We're vagabonds who can't even use
our real names because of past offenses.

36
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:59,900
Is that why you don't care
even if they die?

37
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:03,690
Is Gardar's life worth that much?

38
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:06,360
Is it worth more than
five of my subordinates?

39
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:09,780
Tell me, Thorfinn and Arnheid,

40
00:06:10,490 --> 00:06:12,830
the difference in their worth.

41
00:06:22,710 --> 00:06:25,670
That means there is no difference.

42
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:29,550
-Well then…
-No!

43
00:06:30,130 --> 00:06:32,180
I will have him pay

44
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:35,680
a life for a life!

45
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:23,100
Are you still going to fight?

46
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:26,820
Will you get revenge

47
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,610
for Gardar?

48
00:07:33,610 --> 00:07:37,540
You're the one who cut
Gardar's rope, right Arnheid?

49
00:07:39,370 --> 00:07:42,330
You guys will be punished
for what you did.

50
00:07:43,620 --> 00:07:46,130
I'll tie you up until the master returns--

51
00:08:16,950 --> 00:08:19,580
That's enough! Gardar!

52
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:25,580
If you keep that up he'll die!

53
00:08:26,290 --> 00:08:27,590
Gardar!

54
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:30,800
Damn it! How strong is he?

55
00:08:35,970 --> 00:08:37,680
Gardar!

56
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:41,600
Let go!

57
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:45,350
Gardar!

58
00:08:56,490 --> 00:08:58,120
Gardar…

59
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:02,580
Let's go back, Gardar.

60
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:13,210
It's all right now.

61
00:09:14,260 --> 00:09:18,050
No one is trying to
get in our way anymore.

62
00:09:19,050 --> 00:09:21,560
Hjalti is waiting for us too.

63
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:49,670
Hjalti…

64
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,130
Where

65
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:57,680
is he now?

66
00:10:12,650 --> 00:10:16,900
Your older brother
is looking after him in Birka.

67
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:20,490
I had him take refuge there
before the war began.

68
00:10:22,910 --> 00:10:24,490
I see.

69
00:10:25,490 --> 00:10:28,370
My older brother
is always taking care of me.

70
00:10:29,290 --> 00:10:32,210
When we go to pick up Hjalti,

71
00:10:32,290 --> 00:10:34,750
I have to take a thank you gift.

72
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:41,140
-Excuse me, you there.
-Huh?

73
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:44,850
Is this wagon yours?

74
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:47,100
I would like to borrow it.

75
00:10:48,020 --> 00:10:51,150
-No…
-It's mine.

76
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:54,360
I'll give it to you,

77
00:10:55,070 --> 00:10:56,400
Gardar.

78
00:11:02,410 --> 00:11:05,120
Pardon me for speaking to you
from up here.

79
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,910
What is your name, sir?

80
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:11,290
I'm Sverkel.

81
00:11:12,210 --> 00:11:15,880
Go on, back to your home.

82
00:11:17,380 --> 00:11:20,930
Thank you, Sverkel.

83
00:11:27,930 --> 00:11:29,230
Thorfinn…

84
00:11:30,850 --> 00:11:37,190
Words cannot express my gratitude
for you and Einar.

85
00:11:38,190 --> 00:11:40,570
This is reckless, Arnheid.

86
00:11:41,570 --> 00:11:44,620
Gardar isn't going to…

87
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:52,960
It's fine.

88
00:11:58,590 --> 00:12:00,460
Please send us off.

89
00:12:48,010 --> 00:12:49,390
<i>It's cold.</i>

90
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:54,890
<i>I'm frozen to the core.</i>

91
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:09,830
<i>How pitiful…</i>

92
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:14,080
<i>Such unfortunate beings who were</i>

93
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:17,000
<i>abandoned by the gods.</i>

94
00:14:28,780 --> 00:14:30,200
You are…

95
00:14:32,530 --> 00:14:35,410
You are my new pride and joy.

96
00:14:36,830 --> 00:14:41,210
Hjalti! Hjalti, son of Gardar!

97
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:45,380
I will continue fighting…

98
00:14:46,130 --> 00:14:49,260
so you can take pride in my honor

99
00:14:49,970 --> 00:14:52,890
and so we can become wealthy someday.

100
00:15:55,530 --> 00:15:57,080
One second!

101
00:16:24,730 --> 00:16:25,810
What is it?

102
00:17:18,030 --> 00:17:19,450
For honor

103
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:21,870
and wealth.

104
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,120
Gardar?

105
00:17:33,630 --> 00:17:35,550
How old

106
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:37,970
is Hjalti now?

107
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:40,890
Eight?

108
00:17:41,510 --> 00:17:42,850
Nine?

109
00:17:47,190 --> 00:17:48,350
He's six.

110
00:17:51,270 --> 00:17:52,940
My goodness…

111
00:17:53,610 --> 00:17:57,530
I've lost track of time
ever since I became a slave.

112
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:02,620
Six, huh? I see…

113
00:18:02,700 --> 00:18:03,990
That's too bad.

114
00:18:05,080 --> 00:18:08,370
I couldn't see him
at his most adorable age.

115
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:13,460
He was still one when I parted with him.

116
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:17,130
Man…

117
00:18:18,260 --> 00:18:21,930
He has probably long forgotten about us.

118
00:18:26,020 --> 00:18:31,940
Considering the fact that he's my child,
I bet he's causing quite the mischief.

119
00:18:32,940 --> 00:18:35,530
Like setting fire to the horse's tail.

120
00:18:37,530 --> 00:18:41,280
You did such a thing
when you were a child?

121
00:18:42,030 --> 00:18:45,540
Yeah. My father got so mad at me.

122
00:18:52,420 --> 00:18:54,040
When he becomes old enough,

123
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:58,220
he'll probably say that
he wants to become a Viking.

124
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:00,970
Like all boys do.

125
00:19:06,060 --> 00:19:08,810
But I will not allow that.

126
00:19:24,490 --> 00:19:25,580
Gardar!

127
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:43,180
It's okay.

128
00:19:44,970 --> 00:19:47,220
I'm a little tired, that's all.

129
00:19:49,470 --> 00:19:51,100
Just let me rest.

130
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:35,650
You're sure about this?

131
00:20:35,730 --> 00:20:38,650
Yeah. We've made up our minds.

132
00:20:38,730 --> 00:20:42,530
If we get the iron,
we'll be able to live comfortably.

133
00:20:42,610 --> 00:20:44,450
Your family too.

134
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:52,450
-Okay. I'll go too.
-All right!

135
00:20:55,210 --> 00:20:57,710
Everyone's gathered at the village square.

136
00:20:57,790 --> 00:20:59,710
Come on, let's hurry.

137
00:21:24,860 --> 00:21:26,320
Arnheid…

138
00:21:28,660 --> 00:21:30,280
Hjalti…

139
00:21:33,290 --> 00:21:35,500
I will never

140
00:21:36,710 --> 00:21:39,130
leave you two alone

141
00:21:40,630 --> 00:21:41,500
again…

142
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:35,910
I'm… home…

143
00:23:54,340 --> 00:23:55,390
Welcome home…

144
00:23:57,850 --> 00:23:59,430
Welcome home…

145
00:24:02,060 --> 00:24:03,400
Gardar.

146
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:55,090
<i>"First Course of Action."</i>

147
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:56,010
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita

